Source:  Historical Records
Author:  McNAB
Vol / Page:  1/172
Edition:
Quote:   [Tookee then] introduced [the chief] to me, and after the ceremony of etrouge (joining noses) he

took off his ha-a how ... and put it on my shoulders. In return, I made him a present of an ha-a-how made of green baize decorated with broad arrows.
Notes:  1793 Nov 19 Lieut-Governor King to the Right Hon. Henry Dundas in 1908 McNab Historical Records 1/172

